
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `msggrep` baraye jostojoo kardan dar file-haye `messages` estefade mishavad. File-haye `messages` ob'haee az tarjomeh hastand ke baraye software-ha estefade mishavand ta software be zaban-haye mokhtalef kar konad. Ba `msggrep` shoma mitoonid be donbale matn-haye khass dar in file-ha begardid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `msggrep -i "matn mored nazar" file.po`  --> 🔎 Jostojoo ba bi deghati be horoof bozorg va koochak.
    🔹 `msggrep -n "matn mored nazar" file.po`  --> 🔢 Namayesh shomare khat dar natijeh.
    🔹 `msggrep -w "matn mored nazar" file.po`  --> 🎯 Jostojoo baraye kalameh kamel.
    🔹 `msggrep -r directory` --> 📁 Jostojoo rekursiv dar pooshe-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ msggrep "Hello world" file.po

    🔹 Jostojoo baraye matn "Hello world" dar file `file.po`.

    $ msggrep -i "hello world" file.po

    🔹 Jostojoo baraye matn "hello world" (bi deghati be case) dar file `file.po`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ msggrep -n "Welcome" myapp.po

    🔹  In dastoor matn "Welcome" ra dar file `myapp.po` jostojoo mikonad va shomare khat-haee ke in matn dar anha peida mishavad ra namayesh midahad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `msggrep` command is used for searching within `messages` files. `Messages` files are translation databases used by software to operate in different languages. With `msggrep`, you can search for specific text within these files.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `msggrep -i "text to search" file.po` --> 🔎 Search ignoring case.
    🔹 `msggrep -n "text to search" file.po` --> 🔢 Show line numbers in the output.
    🔹 `msggrep -w "text to search" file.po` --> 🎯 Search for whole words only.
    🔹 `msggrep -r directory` --> 📁 Recursively search through directories.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ msggrep "Hello world" file.po

    🔹 Search for the text "Hello world" in the file `file.po`.

    $ msggrep -i "hello world" file.po

    🔹 Search for the text "hello world" (case-insensitive) in the file `file.po`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ msggrep -n "Welcome" myapp.po

    🔹 This command searches for the text "Welcome" in the `myapp.po` file and displays the line numbers where the text is found.
